Description

This lab contains a path traversal vulnerability in the product image functionality. The application validates that the supplied file path starts with an expected directory, but fails to properly normalize the path, allowing traversal sequences to escape the intended folder.

Objective

Retrieve the contents of the /etc/passwd file.

Steps to Solve
Intercept the request using Burp Suite while loading a product image.
Identify the parameter that contains the full file path (e.g., filename).

Modify the filename parameter to include traversal sequences after the valid prefix:

/var/www/images/../../../etc/passwd
Send the modified request to the server.
Observe that the response contains the contents of the /etc/passwd file.
Conclusion

The application only checks that the path starts with a trusted directory but does not properly resolve or normalize it. This allows attackers to traverse outside the intended directory and access sensitive files.
